In the current implementation text markup is ignored inside the {code}. This is highly inconvenient because if you are using Confluence for technical documentation (like me) and you give a code snippet as an example, you may, a lot of times, want to highlight a portion of the code with bold or something.

Example:

{code}
public EnumerationWrapper( Set set ) {

        if( set == null )
            *set = new HashSet();*

            this.interator = set.iterator();
    }
{code}

In the current implementation "set = new HashSet();" will not be bolded. Neither does {color:red}set = new HashSet();{color} work.

